This is my ultimate @bondisands skin glowing routine including what I use to prep, self tan and maintain!

Absolutely delicious routine that is available @cvsbeauty and let’s you be smooth and bronzed, all year round!!☀️

And as a treat I’m giving away a YEARS WORTH of goodies to one of YOU😍
To WIN:
💙Follow me & @bondisands
💙Like this post and tag a BFF you’d share this prize with in the comments!
💙Giveaway ends 11.59PM CST, August 11
 *T&C’s at https://bit.ly/3yoKUsL 

And of course whatever the skin you’re in you’re beautiful from the inside out and so much more than just you’re physical self…this is just something that I love to do as part of my glow up / self care routine every other week🥰 
.
.
.

node.text:
My babies closet, which I wanted to be the cutest place in the house got out of hand. It literally became a dumping ground and it made me sad everyday. So much so I avoided because I just couldn’t deal with it - and of course that just meant it kept getting worse

Thankfully I found the @homesort ladies🙏And I wanted to make this video for you to share how they helped me create systems so that it’s easier for me to stay organised. Because some of us are just a lil more messy than others🤷‍♀️ and that’s ok😬

But what wasn’t ok was that I let the mess infiltrate my self worth, I started to think I was a mess and let that bring me down and add to the already intense guilt of being a working mom and not having enough hours in the day 

I was hesitant to share all of this because I know there are far bigger issues in the world,  and I’m highly highly aware of my privileges, but if this can help even just one of you feeling this as a new mom in a pandemic or literally anyone feeling overwhelmed - you can ask for help and you’re doing great (virtual hug)🥰

Basically I can’t recommend the @homesort team enough and we love to support female founded companies, so give them a follow, you’ll be obsessed with all the tips, tricks and before and afters✨

#homeorganization #homesort #homeorganising #nurserydesign #nurseryinspiration #montessoriplayroom #montessoriinspired #montessoriathome #organizing #beforeandafterhomeedition

node.text:
#AD| ❤️ In case you forgot, this is your reminder that you are indeed a badass, imperfectly perfect, more than enough, much needed human being

(Side note, I hope my Oscar winning performance gives you a good belly chuckle🤣)

For me it’s been all too easy to forget the great things about me, feel overwhelmed and some days I have to admit (mom guilt central) I miss the pre motherhood freedom and time I could carve out for myself uninterrupted

I quickly realised being a working mom during a pandemic I needed to ask for help. Even though we are told over and over by society that it’s a superpower to multi task, something has to give if you’re burnt out and overtired

I've been enjoying yummy @activiaus yogurts and have re prioritised moments for me throughout the week to feel realigned, recharged and proud of myself for knowing I’m worth it - and you are too!

So if this sounds like something you’d like to try, head over to @activiaus and start your journey💪

#activiaus #guthealth #wellbeing

Joining me and @philipapayne on today's episode is my girl @aimebee of @speakastrology (we've been friends and worked together for years in the fashion industry and shes now turned her passion for Astrology into a degree and new career! Get it B!

Most people don't know but Philip intentionally found out what sign I was before we met and did some reserch so he knew how best to approach me and kinda what to expect as I am a Virgo.

As you can imagine I was blown away, and then finding out he is an aquarious it also made a lot of things make sense haha so here we are trying to learn mre and excited to share it with you!

I found out there is such deeper meaning of self-love, self-care, and self-discovery behind our sign and B did say if you want to get your birth chart done / connect with her to follow and DM her @speakastrology 

Now I'm also super curious what’s your sign???

Do you look into peoples zodiacs before or after you meet them???

Thanks for #SelfFunding with us, sending you all so much love 

.
.
.
.
#astrology #zodiacsigns #couplegoals #relationshipgoals #relationships #relationshipadvice

node.text:
We are back @philipapayne for series 2 of Self Funding

Today we wanted to discuss how we are coping as new parents and chasing our careers. Part of me regrets not taking maternity leave but after feeling overwhelmed I took steps to balance baby and work and want to share how we do this together.

Philip has launched his podcast, educated himself on crypto and we have both diversified and grown our investment portfolios since the pandemic. As a partnership and individuals we realised the importance of constantly creating new goals and figuring out how to best support one another to achieve them.

As you know I got the amazing opportunity to partner with @activiaus an opportunity that fitted so well into my life as gut health has always been a priority of mine and it’s been one of the easiest ways I’ve taken care of myself when at times I’ve felt super burnt out or overwhelmed navigating motherhood because as they say you don’t just bring a baby into the world you also birth parents who have to figure it out too.

Hope you enjoy today’s episode and comment below any tips you have to balance your life as new patents or during this pandemic because I love learning from you!

.
.
.

#SelfFunding #momlife #newmom #parents #parenting #worklifebalance

🥞Monday 
Neutral Relaxed Shacket | Stone

https://bit.ly/2YmMUl1

https://bit.ly/3sYhHCK

🥯Thursday
Asymmetric Dress | Black 
https://bit.ly/3cn1otk

https://bit.ly/36kIPT0

🥑Friday
Shirred Midi Dress | Green Star Print 
https://bit.ly/3a4V72A

🍳Saturday 
Chloe Coated High Waist Skinny Jeans | Black 
https://bit.ly/2NFLuQt
Foo Fighters T-Shirt by Daisy 
https://bit.ly/3ciePuu
Volume Sleeve Belted Shacket | Washed Black
 https://bit.ly/3ab7Kth

🥐Sunday

Hope you enjoyed this little dress up video - we actually filmed it in my garage!

node.text:
If you haven’t heard of Crypto currencies yet you will soon, because it’s happening.
And we don’t want you to miss out - or not know how big of an impact this is having on the world and eventually how we invest, spend and exchange goods and services.

We are by no means experts, please do your own research or work with a financial advisor - we are simply sharing what we are currently learning and excited about and like we said it’s happening right now so we do feel passionate about the opportunity for us all to hold a decentralised currency and the fact Elon Musk and @teslamotors just invested $1.5billion into Bitcoin shows that someone at the forefront of tech believes it’s the future🚀 

Please comment below your experience / knowledge we are all here to learn and share!🙏❤️

#cryptocurrency #cryptotrading #crypto #selffunding

node.text:
✨A lot of you have been asking how @philipapayne and I set healthy boundaries in our relationship❤️

We are definitely not perfect 🤷‍♀️ but we wanted to share how boundary-setting helps us gain a better understanding of each other🙏
 
🍂Each season of life is different so those boundaries may change ♻️ having a strong communication foundation is really important for setting & REsetting those boundaries🙌

⬆️Check out the worksheets in my stories to dive a little deeper into setting boundaries in your relationships!💗

node.title: Self Funding: Ep 10 🔐 Setting Boundaries in Relationships

node.text:
Last Monday @philipapayne and I went LIVE on IG & Tiktok to share some of our favorite partner exercises, but more importantly sharing how we show up and get to the actual workout together because that’s usually the hardest part😬

We are both pretttyyy competitive but we have to use that to challenge each other instead of discourage, and remind one another of how great we feel and all the positive benefits of moving💃

For us it’s important to share how we are feeling physically,🤰Post-partum is a whole other ball game, I definitely rely on philip to motivate me & push me. 

Communication is 🔑 when it comes to working out with your partner. 30 mins/day sounds reasonable but sometimes, after a long day, I have to tell philip I’m just way too tired 😂🤦‍♀️ & of course, he knows when to motivate or give me a lil boost & when to let me rest✌️😴

✏️Try planning & setting aside 30 mins to prioritize your wellness together as a ritual, whatever that looks like and see how you can support each other to help them achieve your well-being goals❤️

node.title: Self Funding: Ep 9 💪Working Out With Your Partner

node.text:
We do our best to choose each other and show up everyday with kindness

And yes we have only known each other 3 years and definitely don’t have all the answers - but I will tell you I’ve had my fair share of serious relationships and this is the first time I’ve felt fully respected, appreciated and loved unconditionally and that didn’t happen by accident

By going into this relationship knowing we are whole and loved no matter what and not having unrealistic expectations for each other because no one is perfect it has helped us build a strong foundation and I hope today’s #SelfFunding episode gives you some insight and takeaways that could help you whether you’re single and hoping to meet someone or currently in a relationship that is maybe challenging

I’ve been there, cried myself to sleep, felt betrayed, wondered if I would ever meet my soul mate or if that’s just BS

I’ve also loved and cherished my single life and never take that time for granted 

Neither of us our perfect, and we don’t expect that - working with those imperfections and supporting each other to be vulnerable and kind to ourselves and each other whilst growing together by sharing our hopes and dreams for our family is the greatest gift - thanks for being you @philipapayne love you and damn this life is so lit with you🔥❤️ 

#loveyou #relationshipadvice #relationships #relationshipgoals #partnership #lifelessons

☀️Summer family dump🍦
1. Spent the 4th with our friends at the lake - I dressed completely in appropriately, sweated my balls off and changed into flats immediately🤣
2. Momma was feelin herself in LA, who else loves an all white look for summer?🤍
3+4. Mom and dad trying to hard to get a family selfie at pool day😬
5. For a about a month now me and P have been making time for weekly date nights, it’s always so special❤️
6. Lake days with our friends are the best, our little man loves the water🥰
7. The day you ate 5 oranges in a row, guess they were hittin🤷‍♀️
8. The Payne fam✨

node.text:
Let me preface this with I don’t believe in cancel culture. Period.

I’ve had many experiences in the fashion industry that have left me questioning if progress will ever happen across the board. And I’m in a white, able body, at a US size 12/14 I have the privilege of being able to shop in most stores. When I do get to work with a brand I usually have to ask are you ready to be more inclusive? 

These pics were taken at a store opening, not only are the clothes cute but I was looking forward to having the discussion of inclusion because there’s a limited size range which I’ve seen @katiesturino flag before (❤️u)

I believe supporting brands into improvement and growth rather than shaming and cancel culture because that feels to me the more positive route for change? But it doesn’t always work - let me know your thoughts!!!

After taking time out my day to go and support the opening I was told I could pick out a cute fit. It soon transpired  after searching the store my size was not available (again I know I’m very privileged as many have to assume their sizes won’t be carried and I get to assume mine is) long story short, I communicated that this was disappointing you’d chosen to invite me and I wanted to have a conversation with the team and even had my agency reach out so we could have a formal discussion of the importance of inclusion

Unfortunately after months of chasing to see if this managed to get noticed or flagged the one response received was “they are discussing it internally” aka they hope I’d go away and drop it?!

We all know staying silent doesn’t create change, I’m still learning how to hold brands accountable in a positive way so they want to do better, listen and learn

I’m speaking to a couple of brands atm who have said they want to and will be increasing sizing so pls brands don’t ignore inclusion, do it because it’s the right thing to do AND ITS GOOD FOR BUSINESS! Me and 67% of women size 14 or over want to wear your clothes!

Also I apologise if this felt at all “whiney” I don’t want to be insensitive to the many other issues going on rn❤️

node.text:
✨🎉Today’s the day🗝 closed on our dream home [pre 1-2 years of renovation] but it’s truly a special space I cannot wait to share the whole process with you🔨
As a woman in business I want to not only want to share these big celebratory moments but also reflect back on all the sacrifices I made to save up to get to this point and the time I took to educate myself around finance, investing and saving

7years ago I moved to the US with $15k of savings and I’ve slowly built wealth and today I closed on my 4th property. Call me boring (I’ve never bought a flashy car, jewellery etc - if that’s your thing cool) but I’ve always enjoyed investing and trying to slowly climb the property ladder by buying homes I can renovate and make a return on. The assumption during all my transactions is that it isn’t ‘my money’ or I’ve seen people comment on my pics saying I’m with P for money - heck he could be with me for that🤣 - yes a woman can be a breadwinner and yes she can have a seat at all the tables.

I am highly aware of my privilege during all these types of convos but would like to feel that I can share more regarding money and investing with you because that’s how we learn and as a female collective we talk a lot less about money and more about appearances and I’d really like to shift that focus - what do you think? Are you down to disrupt?💼💸

I mean we can still talk about body image and I’ll always be flying the ED recovery flag but financial abuse is rife and I’d imagine many of you also have goals for financial freedom and generational wealth (one of my fave content creators is @heyberna and to learn about and carry out my investing I use free @publicapp ) 

And of course wealth isn’t everything - health, happiness and family is always my top priority but money does = choices, security and opportunity and I want to do what I can to share inspo / info on how to support your goals too! 

Soooo what would you like to know about property investing? Pick my🧠 hehe

.
.
.
#femaleinvestors #femalepropertyinvestor #femalepropertydeveloper #femaleentrepreneur #businesswoman #entrepreneurlife #entrepreneurmindset #propertyinvestment #propertyinvestor

node.text:
My babies closet, which I wanted to be the cutest place in the house got out of hand. It literally became a dumping ground and it made me sad everyday. So much so I avoided because I just couldn’t deal with it - and of course that just meant it kept getting worse

Thankfully I found the @homesort ladies🙏And I wanted to make this video for you to share how they helped me create systems so that it’s easier for me to stay organised. Because some of us are just a lil more messy than others🤷‍♀️ and that’s ok😬

But what wasn’t ok was that I let the mess infiltrate my self worth, I started to think I was a mess and let that bring me down and add to the already intense guilt of being a working mom and not having enough hours in the day 

I was hesitant to share all of this because I know there are far bigger issues in the world,  and I’m highly highly aware of my privileges, but if this can help even just one of you feeling this as a new mom in a pandemic or literally anyone feeling overwhelmed - you can ask for help and you’re doing great (virtual hug)🥰

Basically I can’t recommend the @homesort team enough and we love to support female founded companies, so give them a follow, you’ll be obsessed with all the tips, tricks and before and afters✨

#homeorganization #homesort #homeorganising #nurserydesign #nurseryinspiration #montessoriplayroom #montessoriinspired #montessoriathome #organizing #beforeandafterhomeedition
